&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;GLOUCESTERSHIRE HOSPITALS NHS FOUNDATION TRUST&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;HISTOPATHOLOGY DEPARTMENT&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cheltenham General Hospital &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Clerical Team Manager&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 4&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full time - 37.5 hours per week&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span&gt;We have a vacancy for an office manager in this innovative department which is dedicated to quality, professional development and training.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Gloucestershire Hospitals Trust is a modern, forward-thinking Foundation Trust and the Department, which is ISO 15189 accredited and approved by the IBMS for training, is based at Cheltenham General with a hot-lab at Gloucester Royal Hospital. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are a large, busy department, offering a wide range of techniques and are looking for a dynamic leader to manage a clerical team and provide administration support to a team of Consultant Histopathologists. You will be based at Cheltenham General Hospital and should have secretarial and admin experience and experience in leading a team&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further information please contact Andrew Usher or Amy Stone on 0300 422 4400  or e-mail  andrew.usher1@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
